-- Barclays’s China Chairman Qiu Retires After Three Years at Bank
-- B y   C a t h y   C h a n
-- 2013-03-04T02:34:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-04/barclays-s-china-chairman-qiu-retires-after-three-years-at-bank.html
Qiu Zhi Zhong, chairman of greater
China at  Barclays Plc (BARC) ’s investment banking unit, has retired
after spending more than three years at the U.K.’s second-
largest bank, according to a memo obtained by Bloomberg News.  Qiu, also vice chairman of Asia, retired March 1, according
to the memo. Angie Tang, a Hong Kong-based spokeswoman for
Barclays, confirmed the contents of the document. Qiu joined the
firm in 2009 from ABN Amro Holding NV, where he worked for three
years. The memo didn’t mention a replacement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cathy Chan in  Hong Kong  at 
 kchan14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
